<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Aspen Woods</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Located in the southwest quadrant of Calgary, Alberta, Aspen Woods is bordered by 17 Avenue SW in the south and 12 Avenue and Bow Trail SW in the north. 85 Street SW runs along the eastern border, and towards the west is 101 Street SW. Being very close to Downtown Calgary makes Aspen Woods an attractive destination for a long-term dwelling.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">With an average asking price of $1,500,000, homes in Aspen Woods real estate feature luxurious single-family homes in the setting of lush greenery in the form of evergreen trees and well-maintained lawns. Although annexed to the city of Calgary in 1956, Aspen Woods real estate was developed in 2001. Although a majority of the real estate is comprised of spacious single-family homes, there are condos and townhouses as well. With Downtown Calgary being just an 18-minute drive away, Aspen Woods is an ideal place for those who work in the city.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Aspen Woods is located in Ward 6 and represented by Richard Pootmans on the Calgary City Council. Provincially, it is located in the Calgary-West riding and represented by Ken Hughes and federally in the Calgary West riding, represented by Ron Anders.</p>
        </div>
